You don't really need a compression tool for bus plates, they dont have a
preload like a beetle. floor jack works well. I used a magnetic protractor
from sears. $5-$8 range


> I had to do the same thing with my SC. Fortunately, all the PO did was
lower
> the rear be adjusting the spring plates on the torsion bars. I just
followed
> the Bently and readjusted them back to 20 degrees. I built a spring plate
> compression tool just like the one shown in the pictures and a simple
degree
> plate. If anyone is interested in buying them, I made two sets and can
part
> with one for $25. It was a big help to me. If it's beyond anyone's meager
> salary to own one, get with your local club and see if they want to buy it
> for their members.
